SIMPLE: sudden
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sudden
<hw>Sud"den</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sodian</ets>, <ets>sodein</ets>, OF. <ets>sodain</ets>,
<ets>sudain</ets>, F. <ets>soudain</ets>, L. <ets>subitaneus</ets>, fr.
<ets>subitus</ets> sudden, that has come unexpectedly, p. p. of
<ets>subire</ets> to come on, to steal upon; <ets>sub</ets> under,
secretly + <ets>ire</ets> to go. See <er>Issue</er>, and cf.
<er>Subitaneous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Happening without previous
notice or with very brief notice; coming unexpectedly, or without the
common preparation; immediate; instant; speedy.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧O
<xex>sudden</xex> wo!⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Chaucer.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧For fear of
<xex>sudden</xex> death.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sudden</qex> fear troubleth thee.</q> <rj><qau>Job xxii.
10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hastly prepared or employed; quick; rapid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Never was such a <qex>sudden</qex> scholar made.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The apples of Asphaltis, appearing goodly to the <qex>sudden</qex>
eye.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hasty; violent; rash; precipitate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unexpected; unusual; abrupt;
unlooked-for.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sud"den*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sud"den*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sudden</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sudden
<hw>Sud"den</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Suddenly; unexpectedly.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Herbs of every leaf that <qex>sudden</qex> flowered.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sudden</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sudden
<hw>Sud"den</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An unexpected occurrence; a
surprise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>All of a sudden</b></col>, <col><b>On a
sudden</b></col>, <col><b>Of a sudden</b></col></mcol>, <cd>sooner than
was expected; without the usual preparation; suddenly.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How art thou lost! how <qex>on a sudden</qex> lost!</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He withdrew his opposition <qex>all of a sudden</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Thackeray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suddenty</ent>⟦br⟧
